The paper discusses mechanical learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on the internal representation space and learning dynamics of a learning machine, which suggests a connection to topics such as deep learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
